\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 TONE EIGHT}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Behold, the Bridegroom cometh at mid
night, and blessed is that servant whom He shall find watching, but unworthy is he whom He shall find heedless. Beware, therefore, O my soul, lest thou be weighed down with sleep; lest thou be given up to death, and be shut out from the kingdom. But rouse
 thyself and cry: Holy, Holy, Holy art Thou, O God; through the Theotokos have mercy on us.   
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Meditating on that terrible day, O my soul, watch, keeping thy lamp alight and filled with oil; for
 thou knowest not when unto thee shall come the voice, saying: Behold the Bridegroom! Beware, therefore, my soul, lest thou fall into  slumber and be left outside, knocking, as were the five virgins; but wakefully watch, that thou mayest come to meet Chri
s with good oil, and He shall bestow upon thee the divine chamber of His glory. 
\par 
\par Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Theotokion. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Thee, the unassailable wall, confirmation of salvation, O Virgin Theotokos do we supplicate, to destroy the 
counsels of the enemies, to change the sorrows of thy people into joy, to protect thy city, to ensure victory for pious, and to pray for the peace of the world; for thou, O Theotokos, art our hope}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 .
\par 
