\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 TONE TWO}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 
O Thou Who art by nature uncreated, the Fashioner of all, do Thou open our lips that we may proclaim Thy praise while we cry: Holy, Holy, Holy art Thou, O God; through the Theotokos, have mercy on us.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181    
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.
\par 
\par Imitating on earth the Hosts on high, we offer Thee, O Good One, the triumphant song: Holy, Holy, Holy art Thou, O God; through the Theotokos, have mercy on us.
\par 
\par Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 From bed and sleep hast Thou r
aised me up, O Lord; enlighten my mind and heart, and open my lips that I may hymn Thee, O Holy Trinity: Holy, Holy, Holy art Thou, O God; through the Theotokos, have mercy on us.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181     
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 \sect }\sectd \ltrsect\psz1\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 
