\par And if be Great Lent, or the first day of the Apostles fast, or the first day of the Nativity Fast (if it fall on a weekday), we say prayer of St. Ephraim the Syrian, dividing it into three parts and making three prostrations.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs25\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6177181 PRIEST:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 
O Lord and  Master of my life, a spirit of idleness, despondency, ambition, talking give me not.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prostration.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 But rather a spirit of chastity, humble-mindedness, patience, and love bestow up me Thy servant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prostration.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181     
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 Yea, O Lord and King, grant me to see my failings and not condemn my brother; for blessed art Thou unto the ages of amen.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prostration.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Then twelve "reverences" (bows from the waist with the sign of the Cross).}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 With each one we say: O God, cleanse me a sinner..  And then the entire prayer:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 
O Lord and Master of my life, a spirit  idleness, despondency, ambition, idle talking give me not. But rather a spirit of chastity, humble-mindedness, patience, and love bestow on me Thy servant. Yea, O Lord and King, g
rant me to see my failings and not condemn my brother; for blessed art Thou unto the ages of amen.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Prostration.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 \sect }\sectd \ltrsect\psz1\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 
\par Then this  prayer:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par O Sovereign God, the Father Almighty, O Lord, the Only-begotten Son, Jesus Christ and Thou O Holy Spirit, one Godhead, one Power: Have mercy on me a sinner, and by the judgments which Thou knowest, save me, Thine unworthy servant; for blessed art Thou unt
o the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 If it be a Saturday Service this prayer of St. Eustratius:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par Most highly do I magnify Thee, O Lord, for Thou didst take notice of my lowliness 
and hast not delivered me into the hands of mine enemies, but relieved my soul from wants. And now, O Master, let Thy hand shelter me and let Thy mercy descend upon me, for my soul is distracted and pained its departure from this my wretched and filthy  b
o
dy, lest the evil of the adversary overtake it and make it stumble into the darkness for the  unknown and known sins amassed by me in this life. Be merciful unto me, O Master, and let not my soul see the dark  countenances of evil spirits, but let it be r
e
ceived by angels  bright and shining. Glorify Thy holy name and by Thy might set  me before Thy divine judgment seat. When I am being judged, suffer not that the hand of the prince of this world should take hold of me to throw me, a sinner, into depths of
 
Hades, but stand by me and be unto me a savior and mediator, for these bodily torments gladden Thy servants. Have mercy, O Lord, on my soul defiled through passions of this life and receive it cleansed by penitence and confession, for blessed art Thou unt
o the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Then:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par O come let us worship God our King. 
\par O come let us worship and fall down before  Christ our King and God.  
\par O come let us worship and fall down before Christ Himself, our King, and God. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (With Three reverences)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 \sect }\sectd \ltrsect\psz1\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \ltrpar
\s30\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6177181 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs29\insrsid6177181 PSALM 120}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6177181 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 

\par I have lifted up mine eyes to the mountains, from whence cometh my help. My help cometh from the Lord, Who hath made heaven and   the earth. Give not Thy foot unto moving, and He not slumber that   keepeth thee. Behold, He s
hall not slumber nor shall He sleep, He that   keepeth Israel. The Lord shall keep thee: the Lord is thy shelter at thy   right hand. The sun shall not burn thee by nor the moon by night.   The Lord shall keep thee from all evil, the Lord shall guard thy 
soul. The Lord shall keep thy going and thy going out, from henceforth and for evermore.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s30\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid6177181 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\cgrid\noproof\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\insrsid6177181\charrsid6177181 PSALM 133
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 

\par Behold now, bless ye the Lord, all ye servants of the Lord. Ye that  stand in the house of the Lord, in the courts of the house of our God, in the nights li
ft up your hands unto the holies and bless the Lord. The Lord bless thee out of Sion, He that made heaven and the earth.
\par 
\par \sect }\sectd \ltrsect\psz1\linex0\endnhere\titlepg\sectlinegrid360\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj \pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal, have mercy on us. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (Thrice)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the unto the ages of ages. Amen.
\par 
\par O Most Holy Trinity, have mercy on us. O Lord, blot out our sins. O Master, pardon our iniquities. O Holy One, visit and heal our infirmities for Thy name's sake. 
\par 
\par Lord have mercy. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (Thrice) 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par Glory to the Father and to the Son and to the holy Spirit, both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par Our Father, Who art in the Heavens, hallowed by Thy Name. Thy Kingdom come, Thy will be done, on earth as it is in Heaven. Give us this day our daily bread. And forgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors. And lead us not into temptation, but deliver 
us from the evil one. 
\par  
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs25\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6177181 PRIEST:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181   }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 
For Thine is the Kingdom and the power and the glory, of the Father, and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs28\i\f1\insrsid6177181 READER: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  Amen. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 \page And these Troparia:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 TONE 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Remember, O Lord, for T
hou art good, Thy servants and forgive them whatsoever sins they have committed in life; for none is sinless but Thee Who art able to give repose unto them that are departed.
\par 
\par O Thou Who by the depth of Thy Wisdom dost provide all things out of love for ma
nkind, and grantest unto all that which is profitable, O only Creator: Grant rest, O Lord, to the souls of Thy servants; for in Thee have they placed their hope, O our Creator and Fashioner and God.
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Kontakion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 With the saints give rest, O Christ, to the souls of Thy servants, where there is neither sickness, nor sorrow, nor sighing,  but life everlasting.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Theotokion: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 In all generations we c
all thee blessed, O Virgin Theotokos, for in thee the uncontainable Christ our God was pleased to be contained. Blessed are we also, having thee as mediatress; for day and night pleadest thou for us, and the scepters of kingdoms are strengthened by thine 
intercessions. Wherefore in hymns we cry unto thee; Rejoice! O thou who art full of grace, the Lord is with thee.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par 
\par Lord, have mercy. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 Twelve times. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 And this Prayer:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181    
\par 
\par Remember, O Lord, our fathers and brethren who fell asleep in the hope of resurrection unto life eternal, and all those who ended this life in piety and faith, and pardon them every transgression which they have willfully or unwillingly, in word or deed o
r
 thought committed, and settle them in a place of light, a place of refreshment, a place of repose, wherefrom every sickness, sorrow and sighing are banished, and wherein from eternity the light of Thy countenance shineth and gladdeneth all Thy saints. Gr
a
nt unto them and unto us Thy kingdom, and participation in Thine ineffable blessings, and the enjoyment of Thine endless and blessed life. For Thou art the life, and the resurrection, and the repose of Thy departed servants, O Christ our God, and to Thee 
we send up glory, with Thine unoriginate Father, and Thy most holy and good and life-creating Spirit, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.    
\par 
\par Most glorious, Ever-Virgin, Mother of Christ God, present our prayer to thy Son and our God, that through thee He may save our souls.
\par 
\par My hope is the Father, my refuge is the Son, my protection is the Holy Spirit; O Holy Trinity, glory to Thee.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 And these Troparia: 
\par 
\par SIXTH TONE:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par  
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Have mercy on us, O Lord, have mercy on us; / for at a loss for any defense, / this prayer do we sinners offer unto Thee as Master; // have mercy on us.
\par 
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 
\par Lord, have mercy on us; / for we have hoped in Thee, be not angry with us greatly,  / neither remember our iniquities
; / but look upon us now as Thou art compassionate,  / and deliver us from our enemies, / for Thou art our God, and we, Thy people, // all are the works of Thy hands, and we call upon Thy name.
\par 
\par Both now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par The door of compassion open unto us, O blessed Theotokos, / for, hoping in thee, let us not perish; / through thee may we be delivered from adversities, // for thou art the salvation of the Christian race.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs25\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6177181 PRIEST:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 
Have mercy on us, O God, according to Thy great mercy, we pray Thee, hearken and have mercy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\b\i\f1\cf15\insrsid6177181 CHANTERS: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Lord, have mercy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (Thrice)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs25\b\i\f1\fs28\insrsid6177181 PRIEST:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs24\b\f1\fs36\insrsid6177181 
Again we pray that this sacred monastery (or this city). and every monastery, city, town, and every country may be preserved from famine, pestilence, earthquake, fl
ood, fire, the sword, the invasion of aliens, and civil war; that our good and man-loving God may be gracious and favorable, that He may turn away all the wrath stirred up against us,  and deliver us from His righteousness  which hangeth over us, and have
 mercy on us. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\b\i\f1\cf15\insrsid6177181 CHANTERS: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid6177181 Lord, have mercy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\insrsid6177181  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs29\i\f1\cf6\insrsid6177181 (Forty times)
